The exact start date of the Eid al-Fitr festival varies, depending on observations of the new moon by local religious authorities. Northwest China's Qinghai and Gansu provinces started celebrating the festival on Friday, while the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region and Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region are holding festivities today (Saturday).
For more insight into how Muslims in Xinjiang are marking the festival, we can speak to our reporter Wu Guoxiu in Urumqi.Q1. Guo Xiu, what is the atmosphere like in Urumqi today?Q2. You have been following this year's holy month of Ramadan closely, share with us what you have seen over the past week.



